3






333 Middlefield RdMenlo Park, CA 94025


        (650) 473-7888
    






One would hope that Financial Advisers would not have a record of repeated law suits for non-payment of credit card bills, attorney's bills, and a mortgage.  But that is what you will get with Scott Roberts.  Be very careful, do your homework, find out that this man is a liar and don't trust him with your money.







My dad had his money managed here.   When he passed away, it was obvious they had worked with him to make sure everything was completely squared away for my mom...   It was executed with great passion and forethought and the result was a seamless transition for mom.    This success in investing and compassionate administration is priceless.

I have moved all of my investing and banking here and feel all the better for it.   I look forward to a long relationship here.   My experiences so far with banking and retirement account management has been top rate.







These guys are sneaky, deceiving and play games when you try get things done with your account. The VP handling our account, Mr Hogan constantly challenges us when wanting to move money out or change our assest allocation based on needs. While he lives a lavious lifestyle remotely in Hawaii, he almost never contacts the client to check in and do an update on the needs for the portfolio, rather he works the portfolio to collect commisions plus his hidden fees. Then when you want to move the account he claims you are taking money off their operation business costs to keep things running.







One would hope that Financial Advisers would not have a record of repeated law suits for non-payment of credit card bills, attorney's bills, and a mortgage.  But that is what you will get with Scott Roberts.  Be very careful, do your homework, find out that this man is a liar and don't trust him with your money.







            Merrill Lynch
        






